Package: linux-uki-unsigned
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends: ${misc:Depends}, ${shlibs:Depends}, linux-headers-amd64, systemd-ukify
Description: Unsigned Unified Kernel Images for Linux
 This package provides unsigned Unified Kernel Images (UKI) that combine
 the kernel, initramfs, and boot parameters into a single EFI executable.
 .
 UKIs simplify secure boot configurations and provide a more integrated
 boot experience by bundling all boot components together.
 .
 This package contains unsigned images suitable for local use or for
 signing with your own keys.

Package: linux-uki-signed-template
Architecture: amd64
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Template for signed Unified Kernel Images
 This package provides templates and infrastructure for creating signed
 Unified Kernel Images (UKI) for secure boot environments.
 .
 It includes the necessary framework for organizations to add their own
 secure boot keys and generate signed UKIs that can be verified by UEFI
 firmware.
 .
 This package is intended for system administrators and organizations
 that need to deploy securely bootable Linux images across their
 infrastructure.
 